
Ranger Help for: liquify
========================

SYNTAX:      liquify <item>
USAGE:       Any terrain
SLOT COST:   5
BASE SP:     15 sp
SKILL TYPE:  arrow

SUMMARY:    
This skill allows a Ranger to stoke up a searing hot fire and melt
items in it. The Ranger is looking for items with gold or silver in
them, other materials won't melt or just burn up. The soft gold and
silvers easily melt and also make good metals to tip arrows and bolts
with. Gold tipped arrows and bolts are extremely accurate, increasing
chances for hitting critical areas of the body. Silver tipped arrows
and bolts are accurate, but not as accurate as gold tipped arrows and
bolts, but they are less costly. Once you melt down an item, a nugget
of gold or silver will be left. The size of the nugget will be
dependent on how big the original item was. How big the nugget is also
determines how many arrows or bolts can be tipped with it. You can only
liquify items if there is a stove or furnace nearby. A campfire wouldn't
get hot enough. 

        Once you get the nugget, you can "goldtip <arrow/bolt>" or
        "silvertip <arrow/bolt>" depending on which type of nugget
        you have. You can liquify any object with gold or silver in
        it, but weapons and objects will generally leave smaller 
        nuggets than will armours...meaning less tippings per
        nugget. Also, if the liquified object has multiple materials
        in it, the resulting nugget will be smaller.

NOTE: I have to manually add furnace rooms, so if one you think you should
      be supported isn't, lemme know. The more the better..:)

